config PICOCALC_LCD_DRM
	tristate "PicoCalc TinyDRM LCD driver"
	depends on DRM && SPI && DRM_MIPI_DBI
	help
	  Enable the TinyDRM-based driver for the PicoCalc ILI9488 SPI
	  panel. This provides a DRM/KMS interface (via mipi-dbi) so
	  userspace can use the kmsdrm backend instead of the legacy
	  framebuffer driver.
